Bilkul. Ab tumhare current project ko dekhte hue, yeh **practical development plan** hai — beginner-friendly, step by step, aur tumhare existing FastAPI + React + MongoDB setup ke hisaab se.

# Project goal

**Study Material Sharing Platform**

* normal users signup/signin kar sakein
* admin alag signin kare
* admin dashboard me real users show hon
* admin user CRUD kar sake
* baad me materials CRUD add ho

---

# Phase 1 — Auth system

Ye tum almost kar chuki ho.

## Frontend

* landing page
* signup page
* user signin page
* admin signin page

## Backend

* `POST /signup`
* `POST /signin`
* `POST /admin/signin`

## Database

`users` collection me fields:

```json
{
  "fullName": "",
  "email": "",
  "phone": "",
  "password": "",
  "role": "user",
  "status": "active"
}
```

## Rules

* signup par role always `"user"`
* admin manual DB se banta hai
* admin signin par backend role verify karega

---

# Phase 2 — Admin dashboard (users management)

Ye ab tumhara current next step hai.

## Frontend pages

* `AdminDashboard.jsx`
* `AdminDashboard.css`

## Admin dashboard me kya ho

* total users card
* registered users table
* edit button
* delete button
* add user button
* modal for add/edit

## Backend routes

* `GET /users`
* `POST /users`
* `PUT /users/{user_id}`
* `DELETE /users/{user_id}`

## Important rule

* dashboard me **admin khud show na ho**
* isliye `GET /users` me filter:

```python
{"role": {"$ne": "admin"}}
```

---

# Phase 3 — Admin CRUD complete

Ab users CRUD ko proper bana do.

## Add user

Admin dashboard se new user add kare:

* full name
* email
* phone
* password
* role
* status

## Edit user

Admin user ka:

* full name
* email
* phone
* role
* status
  update kar sake

## Delete user

Admin user delete kar sake

## Backend validation

* duplicate email allowed na ho
* admin admin ko delete na kare
* invalid id handle ho

---

# Phase 4 — User dashboard

Auth aur admin ke baad user side build karo.

## User dashboard pages

* welcome/dashboard
* profile
* my uploads
* saved materials

## Features

* user apna profile dekhe
* apne uploaded materials dekhe
* saved items dekhe

Abhi dummy bhi ho sakta hai, baad me backend connect karna.

---

# Phase 5 — Study materials module

Project ka main business feature ye hai.

## Material fields

```json
{
  "title": "",
  "description": "",
  "subject": "",
  "semester": "",
  "tags": [],
  "fileUrl": "",
  "uploadedBy": "",
  "downloadsCount": 0,
  "likes": [],
  "createdAt": ""
}
```

## Backend routes

* `POST /materials`
* `GET /materials`
* `GET /materials/{id}`
* `PUT /materials/{id}`
* `DELETE /materials/{id}`

## Frontend pages

* upload material page
* explore materials page
* material detail page
* my materials page

---

# Phase 6 — Admin materials management

Jab materials aa jayein, admin ko bhi materials manage karne do.

## Admin kya karega

* all materials dekhe
* inappropriate material delete kare
* optional approve/reject system

## Routes

* `GET /admin/materials`
* `DELETE /admin/materials/{id}`
* optional `PATCH /admin/materials/{id}/approve`

---

# Phase 7 — Search and filters

Ab platform useful lagne lagega.

## Explore page pe

* search by title
* filter by subject
* filter by semester
* sort by latest

---

# Phase 8 — Save, like, comment

Ye interaction features hain.

## Backend

* `POST /materials/{id}/save`
* `POST /materials/{id}/like`
* `POST /materials/{id}/comment`

## Frontend

* save button
* like button
* comments section

---

# Phase 9 — Security improvement

Abhi tum basic learning phase me ho, lekin next major upgrade ye hoga:

## Abhi

* plain password
* no JWT
* no protected routes

## Baad me karna

* password hashing
* JWT authentication
* protected admin routes
* current user session

---

# Recommended folder structure

## Frontend

```bash
src/
  App.jsx
  App.css
  signup.jsx
  signup.css
  signin.jsx
  signin.css
  AdminSignin.jsx
  AdminSignin.css
  AdminDashboard.jsx
  AdminDashboard.css
```

## Backend

Abhi single `main.py` theek hai.
Baad me split karna:

```bash
fastapi_backend/
  main.py
  routes/
    auth_routes.py
    admin_routes.py
    material_routes.py
```

